Method Detail

load

public void load(File file)
          throws Exception
Description copied from interface: PluginType
Load method that is called when a file that matches the extension specified is found in plugins directory. If this plugin requires manual adding (IE JavaPlugin) then it must set the name to null so it can be ignored

Implementations of this must completly setup the Plugin, parsing all avalible infomration. The plugin must then be able to be activated by PluginType.invoke(java.lang.String[], Quackbot.Bot, Quackbot.info.BotEvent)

Specified by:
load in interface PluginType
Parameters:
file - The file that contains the script
Throws:
Exception - Any exception encountered while parsing. The command will not be added

invoke

public void invoke(String[] args,
                   Bot bot,
                   BotEvent msgInfo)
            throws Exception
Description copied from interface: PluginType
This is called when the command is requested. This is executed in a seperate thread, so the current thread can be paused without affecting bot operation.

Specified by:
invoke in interface PluginType
Parameters:
args - Any arguments the user passes
bot - The bot that sent the command. Note: Services should expect this to be null.
msgInfo - The BotEvent that contains all message info
Throws:
Exception - If an exception is encountered, it MUST thrown up the chain to be reported as an error.
